Improve your shooting, your rifle, and get compliant all at the same time!
• 100% American made single stage trigger group with machined release surfaces that offers a smooth and consistent trigger pull unlike anything you will find on standard AK triggers. 
• The top profile of the hammer has been optimized to eliminate the bolt carrier hang up that occurs frequently with other hammers and provides a smoother operation without the need of polishing the hammer. 
• The trigger uses a double hook design with an innovative relief cut which allows it to be used in receivers designed to only accept single hook triggers. This gives the operator the option to have the strength and control of a double hook trigger in firearms originally designed to only accept single hook triggers. 
• The disconnector has also been optimized to eliminate trigger slap and “folding” of the engagement surface seen on many other trigger groups during high round count tests. 
• The RAK-1 Enhanced Trigger Group has been properly heat treated and hardened to minimize wear and passed a 15,000 round endurance test. 
• Each trigger group will include a Hammer, Trigger and Disconnector which count as three U.S. 922r compliant parts. The RAK-1 Enhanced Trigger Group will also include a Hammer Spring, Disconnector Spring and a Trigger Sleeve which allows the Trigger/Disconnector to be pre-assembled before dropping into the rifle. 
• The RAK-1 is a great upgrade to any AK style rifle while maintaining the traditional reliability of a stock trigger. 
• Fits CENTURY ARMS WASR, C39, RAS47, AK63D and many other AK rifle and pistol variants.

This is an excellent condition Browning Medallion A Bolt II rifle chambered in 300 WSM, the serial number indicates that is was manufactured in 2011 and features a 26" barrel.  Excellent deer rifle with long range capabilities.  Includes detachable magazine, scope bases, scope rings.  Scope pictured is NOT included in the sale.

The classic Browning A-Bolt (often referred to as the A-Bolt II) delivers dependable, pinpoint accuracy that exceeds the stringent standards of the modern rifleman. The renowned A-Bolt has been produced in popular chamberings, materials and finishes to satisfy your needs in any hunting or shooting situation.

A very sophisticated bolt action - 
With a short 60° lift, the bolt incorporates a non-rotating bolt sleeve that runs the full length of the bolt. When unlocked, three guide ribs on the bolt sleeve align with the three locking lugs to allow the bolt to slide smoothly. When locked, these three lugs provide massive bolt strength. The A-Bolt II feeds very smoothly because of its unique, patented cartridge depressor that stays in position, independent of the bolt rotation, as the bolt slides gently over the cartridges in the magazine. The bolt face is recessed, completely surrounding the cartridge base. A cocking indicator located at the rear of the bolt offers visual and tactile firing pin status.

Barrel -
The barrel is free floating and glass bedded at the recoil lug and front of receiver to maintain the proper spacing around the barrel for consistent accuracy. The recessed muzzle crown helps protect the rifling. Barrels are triple checked for interior finish, straightness and air-gauged for uniformity.

Trigger -
A chrome-plated trigger sear provides cleaner, crisper trigger pull. Screw adjustable and pre-set at approximately 4 lbs.

Magazine - 
Hinged floorplate with detachable box magazine makes it simple and fast to load a spare magazine.

Magazine Capacity - 
WSM: Three in magazine, one in chamber.

title: For Sale:  Bersa Thunder, other overpriced guns, etc.
postcontent:
I'm noticing alot of folks here seem to think their used guns are somehow worth NIB retail, or more so, MSRP.

They're not.

Normally I just ignore it, because its not like anyones MAKING me buy your gun for such prices, but this is getting silly people.


For example, is the Bersa Thunder .380 listed for next to $400.Those guns, USED, aren't worth more then $300 (and thats being generous), period. 

I hate to call ya out, but c'mon, thats ridiculous.
For $400 bucks, someone could go over to gunbroker and have their choice of these guns BNIB, with the baseline model not being over $280, again- BRAND NEW.
The particular model in question with the gold goes for $315, BNIB.

Theres no way those grips make it worth such a high premium.Your basically saying you have $100+ dollar walnut grips. On your USED $275 gun.

 Seriously?

And this guy aint alone, by any means.

People come here to find a bargain on used guns, not pay more then they would at the FFL. NOT to pay more then retail or MSRP and THEN cover YOUR FFL tax. And plenty of folks like me love shopping here, have cash and like to add nice stuff to our collections- but then some people wonder why their listing is ignored, sitting on the list month after month...... 

When you drive a car off the lot, it immediately loses value. Same with when you shoot your gun, the moment you do that, its USED, it may be LIGHTLY used, but its still USED. 

Nobody sells used cars for retail. Take a hint.

Please, unless your gun is (actually) RARE, as in, not being made any more, collectors items, professionally customized, absolutely BNIB (the LNIB stuff is still USED, guys), or otherwise has accessories that come with to add value, be FAIR about your prices, and if you do not know the value of your gun, LOOK IT UP before listing it.

Before you list your stuff, do yourself (if you actually want to sell your gun, and aren't just listing it to appease the 'ol lady) and everyone else a favor and go check out what your USED gun sells for over on gunbroker.

This site isn't for people trying to make a profit off the ignorance of others, its for firearms aficionados to trade guns and for people to save a buck buying used.

No Shipping
Buyer must meet following requirements: at least 21 years old, have a valid Indiana Drivers License, and I prefer to see a License To Carry Handgun (LTCH)
*must be able to legally own firearms

CZ Rami 9mm
- good used condition, has some wear marks around front sight, nothing major
- around 500 rounds fired by me, unknown before that as I bought it used
- manual safety
- has night sights (still bright)
- has the following Cajun Gun Works upgrades: Short Reset System (SRS-1 w/13# hammer spring), 85 combat trigger w/overtravel adjustment, reduced power trigger return spring, floating trigger pin (ALL ORIGINAL PARTS WILL BE INCLUDED)
- wolff +15% extra power magazine spring in the 14rd mag (to improve reliability with hollow points)
- comes with (1) 10rd mag and (1) 14rd mag (I do not have the box or any paperwork)

$525
